{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:job.6",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 6,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 6",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 6 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.6.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:2",
      "text": "Oh that one would indeed weigh the wrath that is upon me, and take up my griefs in a balance together!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.6.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:3",
      "text": "And verily they would be heavier than the sand by the seashore: but, as it seems, my words are vain.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.6.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:4",
      "text": "For the arrows of the Lord are in my body, whose violence drinks up my blood: whenever I am going to speak, they pierce me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.6.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:5",
      "text": "What then? will the wild ass bray for nothing, if he is not seeking food? or again, will the ox low at the manger, when he has fodder?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.6.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:6",
      "text": "Shall bread be eaten without salt? or again, is there taste in empty words?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.6.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:7",
      "text": "For my wrath cannot cease; for I perceive my food as the smell of a lion to be loathsome.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.6.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:8",
      "text": "For oh that he would grant my desire, and my petition might come, and the Lord would grant my hope!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.6.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:9",
      "text": "Let the Lord begin and wound me, but let him not utterly destroy me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.6.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:10",
      "text": "Let the grave be my city, upon the walls of which I have leaped: I will not shrink from it; for I have not denied the holy words of my God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.6.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:11",
      "text": "For what is my strength, that I continue? what is my time, that my soul endures?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.6.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:12",
      "text": "Is my strength the strength of stones? or is my flesh of brass?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.6.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:13",
      "text": "Or have I not trusted in him? but help is far from me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.6.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:14",
      "text": "Mercy has rejected me; and the visitation of the Lord has disregarded me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.6.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:15",
      "text": "My nearest relations have not regarded me; they have passed me by like a failing brook, or like a wave.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.6.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:16",
      "text": "They who used to reverence me, now have come against me like snow or congealed ice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.6.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:17",
      "text": "When it has melted at the approach of heat, it is not known what it was.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.6.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:18",
      "text": "Thus I also have been deserted of all; and I am ruined, and become an outcast.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.6.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:19",
      "text": "Behold the ways of the Thæmanites, ye that mark the paths of the Sabæans.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.6.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:20",
      "text": "They too that trust in cities and riches shall come to shame.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.6.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:21",
      "text": "But ye also have come to me without pity; so that beholding my wound ye are afraid.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.6.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:22",
      "text": "What? have I made any demand of you? or do I ask for strength from you,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.6.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:23",
      "text": "to deliver me from enemies, or to rescue me from the hand of the mighty ones?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.6.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:24",
      "text": "Teach ye me, and I will be silent: if in anything I have erred, tell me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.6.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:25",
      "text": "But as it seems, the words of a true man are vain, because I do not ask strength of you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.6.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:26",
      "text": "Neither will your reproof cause me to cease my words, for neither will I endure the sound of your speech.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.6.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:27",
      "text": "Even because ye attack the fatherless, and insult your friend.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.6.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:28",
      "text": "But now, having looked upon your countenances, I will not lie.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.6.29",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:29",
      "text": "Sit down now, and let there not be unrighteousness; and unite again with the just.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.6.30",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:30",
      "text": "For there is no injustice in my tongue; and does not my throat meditate understanding?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
